      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "I doubt it is fixed, the patch I proposed is breaking the binaries, and AFAIK it hasn't been fixed upstream in another way.\r\n\r\nUnless your executable has some explicitly exported symbols, the relocation table will be missing, and this will cause the executable to be flagged with `IMAGE_FILE_RELOCS_STRIPPED`, so Windows won't enable ASLR.",
